   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE EXPERIENCE OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>GOD S ORGANIC SALVATION EQUALING REIGNING IN CHRIST S LIFE MESSAGE FOUR REIGNING IN LIFE 1 IN DYING WITH ADAM AND LIVING WITH CHRIST,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>IN BEING OVERCOMING IN ALL CIRCUMSTANCES,</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>AND IN LIVING A GRAFTED LIFE WITH CHRIST OUTLINE In dying with Adam: Our natural life needing to be terminated with Adam in our co-death with Christ Rom 6:3, 4a, 5a, 6-8a; Gal 2:20a; Eph 4:22.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Our natural life needing to be annihilated with Adam in our co-death with Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In living with Christ Rom 6:4b, 5b, 8b; Gal 2:20b: Our natural life needing to be raised with Christ in His resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Our natural life needing to be renewed with Christ in His resurrection Eph 4:23-24; 2 Cor 4:16; 5:17.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In being overcoming in all circumstances Rom 8:31-39; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>1 Cor 15:54-57: Needing to be more than conquering in our overcoming with Christ in all circumstances: The love of God Rom 8:39 is the source of His salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>In His salvation this love to us has become the love of Christ v. 35 , which will accomplish God s complete salvation in us through the grace of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>God s enemy attacks us with all kinds of sufferings and calamities Rom 8:35-36 ; however, because of our response to the love of God in Christ, these attacks have become benefits to us v. 28 . Hence, we more than conquer in all these calamities v. 37 . Needing to be all-transcending in our overcoming with Christ in all circumstances: Christ s resurrection was His victory, which will accomplish the ultimate and complete victory in resurrection for us who believe in Him and participate in His resurrection 1 Cor 15:54.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Christ s victory should not only be an accomplished fact for us to receive; it should also become our daily experience in life through the union of the resurrected Christ as the life-giving Spirit 1 Cor 15:45b with our spirit as one spirit 6:17 that we may be all-transcending in our overcoming with Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>In living a grafted life with Christ Rom 11:17-24: To live the life of the new creation in our being grafted with Christ: Becoming a new creation in Christ 2 Cor 5:17.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Walking by the Spirit according to the rule of being a new creation Gal 6:15-16; 5:25.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Putting on the new man Eph 2:15; 4:23-24.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Experiencing the renewing of the new man Col 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To reign in eternity in our being grafted with Christ 2 Tim 2:12; Rev 20:4, 6; 22:5.</S>
   </TEXT>
